The family of former education CS George Magoha has arrived at Lee funeral home. The body of Magoha is expected to be taken to the morgue for preservation. The former CS died on Tuesday at the Nairobi, Hospital. In a statement by the CEO James Nyamongo, Magoha first collapsed at home. He was rushed to the hospital where he was pronounced dead after efforts to resuscitate him failed. "It is with great regret that we announce the sudden and untimely demise of Professor George Magoha this evening at The Nairobi Hospital," The Nairobi HospitalÂ  CEO James Nyamongo said in a statement. "Magoha collapsed at home and was rushed to the Nairobi Hospital A and E. Efforts to resuscitate him were unsuccessful."